ONTARIO SECURITIES COMMISSION RULE 45-501
ONTARIO PROSPECTUS AND REGISTRATION EXEMPTIONS 

2.4 Security of a co-operative 
        The prospectus requirement does not apply to a distribution of a security issued by a corporation to which the Co-operative Corporations Act applies. 

2.5 Membership share of a credit union –
        The prospectus requirement does not apply to a distribution of a membership share of a credit union within the meaning of the Credit Unions and Caisses Populaires Act, 1994

2.6 Security of a credit union – 
        (1) The prospectus requirement does not apply to a distribution of a security issued to its members by a credit union to which the Credit Unions and Caisses Populaires Act, 1994 applies.
        (2) The prospectus requirement does not apply to a distribution of a security issued to its members or the members of its member credit unions by a league to which the Credit Unions and Caisses Populaires Act, 1994 applies. 


       